article.headline: Drexel 89, Quinnipiac 72
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Phil Goss scored 25 points and Kenell Sanchez added 21, both career highs, as Drexel defeated Quinnipiac 89-72 Monday. Jeremiah King added 14 points and Sean Brooks had 15 rebounds for Drexel (2-3), which hit on 12 of 25 from 3-point range. Rashaun Banjo had 19 points and Rob Monroe 17 for the Bobcats (2-4), whose next two games are at Connecticut and Notre Dame. Leading 34-32 at the half, Drexel scored on 10 of its first 12 possessions at the start of the second half to take a 57-44 advantage. Quinnipiac rallied to within 75-66 on two free throws by Monroe with 4:07 to play, but Goss hit a trey and Sanchez scored on a jumper and the Bobcats never threatened again. The Bobcats jumped out to a 15-6 early lead, and led 21-13 before going five minutes without scoring, allowing Drexel to tie it at 21-21. Drexel was 12 for 27 in the first half, while the Bobcats were 11 for 31.
